args: No matter how much we attack this thing,\nit doesn't slow him at all!
This is a real tough one.\nEveryone, keep your distance!
If we let up, it'll just start healin'.\nWe need to strike now!
No! It's trying to run away!
Don't worry about me—just focus on\nour ugly friend over there!
Goodness, that was quite the ordeal.
Show me your back, Ranzal.\nYou clearly are in need of healing.
Ranzal, why do you always INSIST\non charging in alone like that?!
It always ends up with you almost\ngetting killed!
That is no excuse to run off unaided.
Hey, there's no need to be so harsh.\nI mean, we all know how strong he is.
That may be so—but we're still going to\nworry about him. It's what friends do.
Sorry, guys. I just never wanna miss\na chance when it shows itself.
That's all well and good when you're\nfighting alongside us.
But you're a commander now. A leader.
If you run off alone like you just did,\nit's going to unsettle your troops.
Guess I didn't think of that.
You should learn how to work WITH your\ntroops when you're out there with them.
If you wish people to obey and respect\nyou, you must be more composed.
All right, all right! I get it.
I'll work on improvin' as a commander.
Although I got no idea how to start\ndoin' that, if I'm honest...
Is bein' a commander about orderin'\npeople around all dignified?
Let's do this, guys! PARTY TIME!
Woohoo! I'm gonna fire at will!
Anyone in our way is gonna pay!\nWhoop-a-dee-doooooo!
I need to be more calculatin'.\nSee the big picture, like.
Soldiers on the right, stand by!\nHalt the enemy vanguard in its tracks!
Soldiers on the left, flank the enemy!\nThey won't see you coming while they\ndeal with the troops in front of them!
And once they're surrounded,\nwe spring the ambush!
We've cornered our enemies like rats,\nsir. What are your orders?
...Wait, no. That ain't a time for a charge.
Damn it! No matter how much I think\nabout this, I can't find the answer.
I feel like I've thought about it too much\nand now nothin' makes sense.
Damn it! What's the most ＂commander＂\nthing for me to do here?!
Think on it. Think on what you—and only\nyou—can do in this situation.
Why do pops's words have to come\ninto my head at a time like this?
What can I do that no one else can?
Hate to admit I owe my pops for somethin',\nbut I guess I do for this.
You know it. Sounds like it's a type\nlike that one we took down earlier.
Now I'm gonna show everyone how\nthe new Ranzal commands!
This is the same kind of fiend as the one\nwe fought last time.
I know that you're all exhausted,\nbut we need to strike right away.
I'm sorry for runnin' off on my own\nin that last fight.
So that's why I'm gonna tell ya in advance\nwhat I'm doin' this time.
All right. We're counting on you.
We do the same thing as last time.\nI'm gonna charge in and grab 'em,\nthen all of you attack!
I'm countin' on ya. Now let's move out!
He's seriously just gonna do the\nexact same thing as last time?
Never mind that now—just follow him!
Calling this a plan is an insult\nto the very concept of planning.
I don't have the faintest idea what\nthat man is thinking anymore.
Whew! That takes care of that.
Thanks a million, everybody!\nThat went off without a hitch.
You mean your ＂plan＂? The one where you\nsimply charge off like a madman?
That's the one! See, I knew that if I\ncharged, I'd draw all the attention.
With my strength—and this armor—I can\nhandle whatever a fiend throws at me.
And how is this ANY different than\nwhat you were doing before?
I know I'm a commander now,\nbut I gotta keep doin' what I do best.
And that means usin' this bod\nlike a giant battering ram.
They look at me, then you guys wallop 'em\nwhile they're distracted. Perfect, yeah?
Do you honestly believe the job of a\ncommander is to serve as cannon fodder?
'Course not! I got plenty of other skills\nI can bring to bear in a fight.

I'm a former merc! I hear what's goin' on
in villages all across the continent,
I know about fiends and how they live,
I can read the flow of battle...
So who better to guide you guys on all\nthis stuff than a seasoned pro like me?
I suppose we have been saved by\nyour judgment a number of times.
Yeah, Ranzal's got us out of more pinches\nthan a crab-claw buffet.
I know what I can do—I just had to\nwork out how to use those skills\nfor the good of everyone.
If I put myself in harm's way, my troops\nwill believe in me and stand by me.
See? I ain't just doin' stuff without\nthinking—there's a reason for it.
So this is how you're going to command?
Givin' orders from the back\njust don't suit me.
I suppose that means we're forever\ndoomed to worry, but I can't say\nyour arguments are unreasonable.
So in the end, we are right back\nwhere we started.
Bwaa ha ha! Sorry if ya thought I was\ngonna make some huge change.
But I want everyone at my back while\nI wallop chumps from the front.
